      "description": "The planar pentabox $(3,1,4)$: 7 vertices, 8 edges, $L=2$. Two trivalent vertices connected by chains of 3, 1 and 4 edges. For generic kinematics $\\mathrm{Gr}^W_6 H^6(X_{(3,1,4);D};\\mathbb{Q})$ is pure Tate and $W_4 H^6$ is mixed Tate; for $D\\ge 4$, $\\mathrm{Gr}^W_5 H^5(X_{(3,1,4);4};\\mathbb{Q})$ is $H^1(E)(-2)$ for an elliptic curve. The Picard-Fuchs operator $L_{(3,1,4);4}$ computed via the extended Griffiths-Dwork algorithm is irreducible of order 4 and Liouvillian, and therefore does not detect this elliptic curve in middle cohomology.",
